Below two new APIs to be created.

Get Default State is now not required, because POST Validation API takes care of it. when we just give state code, the API returns default state.

Hence this API looks redundant

* -API to get Default state name-
** -GET /v1/countries/{country_code}/states/{state_code}/default-
** -The logic for deciding the default state for the state code is as below (Applicable for v2 countries only)-
*** -Select the active state based on default_language_id.-
*** -If no default_language_id is available then select the state based on language weightage.-
** -Response:-
{noformat}{
    "code": "TX",
    "selectable": true,
    "name": "Texas",
    "languageCode": "en",
    "type": "State"
}{noformat}




+*API to validate state*+

POST /v1/countries/{country_code}/state/validations

*Request:*

{noformat}{  
  "statecode": "TX",  
  "state": "Texas"
}{noformat}

Both State Code and state name are optional.



*Response:*

If both values are provided and both are valid, then the response will be

{noformat}{
  "state": "Texas",
  "statecode": "TX",
  "outcome": "VALID"
}{noformat}

If both values are provided and both are Invalid or any one is Invalid, then the response will be

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "INVALID",
  "error":"<Error Message>"
}{noformat}



If only state code is provided and it is Valid, then the response will be,

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "VALID",
  "state": "<Default State name>",   
  "statecode": "TX"
}{noformat}



If only state name is provided and it is Valid and if it is v1 country, then the response will be,

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "VALID",
  "state": "Texas",   
  "statecode": "TX" --> return the first match.
}{noformat}

If only state name is provided and it is Valid and if it is v2 country and if it has only one matching state code, then the response will be,

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "VALID",
  "state": "Texas",   
  "statecode": "TX" --> return the matching code.
}{noformat}

If only state name is provided and it is Valid and if it is v2 country and if it has multiple matching state codes, then the response will be,

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "INVALID",
  "error":"Found multiple state code for the given state name - Texas"
}{noformat}



If both values are not provided, and if the country does not require states, then the response will be

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "VALID"
}{noformat}

If both values are not provided, and if the country requires states, then the response will be

{noformat}{
  "outcome": "INVALID",
  "error": "State or state code is required for country ['US']"
}{noformat}

Response code will be 200 if the country is valid otherwise 404.

