column33:
When we release a new version of Address Service, we need to delete the snapshot war files that we uploaded to RSI:Artifacts during the development process. To do this, we need to add a cleanup step to the Jenkins job if the build is a release.

Example of CMS Cleanup: 
{code}
        if(isRelease) {
            // Delete snapshot artifacts of release version
            withCredentials([usernamePassword(credentialsId: 'cust_signup_jenkins',
              passwordVariable: 'PASSWORD', usernameVariable: 'USERNAME')]) {
                def repoPath = "customer-maven-local/com/rackspace/customer/service"
                def modules = ["customer-service", "customer-service-adminwar", "customer-service-common",
                               "customer-service-jobwar", "customer-service-war"]
                modules.each { module ->
                    def snapshotArtifactsUrl = "https://artifacts.rackspace.net/artifactory/${repoPath}/${module}/${version}"
                    sh("curl --tlsv1.2 -u${USERNAME}:${PASSWORD} -XDELETE ${snapshotArtifactsUrl}")
                }
            }
        }
 {code}

